  <h2>Pioneering IT Solutions: The Genesis of HCL Technologies</h2>
  
  <h3>Founding Visionaries</h3>
  <p>Founded in 1976 by Shiv Nadar and a group of visionary engineers, HCL Technologies emerged as a trailblazer in the IT industry, originally focusing on personal computers.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Evolution into IT Powerhouse</h3>
  <p>Initially named Microcomp Limited, the company underwent a transformative journey, becoming Hindustan Computers Limited (HCL) in 1976. In 1991, HCL Technologies emerged, specializing in software services.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Strategic Growth and Global Expansion</h2>
  <h3>IPO Milestone</h3>
  <p>In 1999, HCL Technologies marked a significant milestone by going public, issuing 142 crore shares. The company swiftly expanded its operations globally, setting up offshore development centers and acquiring Gulf Computers Inc. in 2002.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Noteworthy Acquisitions</h3>
  <p>From strategic acquisitions like Actian in 2018 to absorbing select IBM products in 2019, HCL Technologies has consistently expanded its portfolio, reaching a remarkable $10 billion in revenue in 2021.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Evolution into HCLTech - A Brand for the Future</h2>
  <h3>A Strategic Rebranding</h3>
